# List → detail back navigation

Whenever a page shows a **list of items** and each item links to a **detail view**, you must add back navigation in both directions.

## Rules

1. **List pages** — Add a `BackLink` at the top of the page (above the title) pointing to the logical parent route (e.g. `/feed`).
2. **Detail pages** — Add a `PageBackLink` at the top that returns to the list the user came from.
3. **Pass navigation state** on every list-item link so the detail page knows where to go back.

## Implementation

Use shared helpers in `src/navigation.ts` and `src/components/BackLink.tsx`:

```tsx
import { BackLink, PageBackLink } from '../components/BackLink'
import { listItemBackState } from '../navigation'

// List page
<BackLink to="/feed" label="Back to feed" />

// List item link
<Link
  to={`/users/${user.id}`}
  state={listItemBackState('/following', 'Back to following')}
>

// Detail page
<PageBackLink defaultTo="/feed" defaultLabel="Back to feed" />
```

## Checklist for new list → detail flows

- [ ] List page has `BackLink` to parent
- [ ] Item links include `state={listItemBackState(backTo, backLabel)}`
- [ ] Detail page renders `PageBackLink` with sensible defaults
- [ ] Back control is the first element inside the page `<section>`

Do not rely on browser history (`navigate(-1)`); use explicit routes via `listItemBackState`.

Reference: `FollowingPage`, `DiscoverPage`, `ProfilePage`, `PostDetailPage`, `FeedPage`.
